  <section class="service-content" id="iot-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Electronic Systems & IoT Services</h2>
      <p>
        The UAE's smart city ambitions — from Dubai's Smart City initiative to
        NEOM-adjacent developments and the rapid expansion of industrial zones
        across Ras Al Khaimah and Abu Dhabi — are creating substantial demand
        for connected hardware, embedded systems, and IoT platforms that can
        operate reliably in demanding physical environments. Whether it is a
        building automation system for a new commercial tower, an industrial
        monitoring platform for a manufacturing facility, or a fleet of
        connected environmental sensors for a smart campus, the engineering
        challenge is the same: making hardware, firmware, and cloud software
        work together seamlessly and securely at scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        GeneralSoft bridges the hardware-software boundary in ways that most
        software development companies cannot. Our team includes engineers with
        embedded systems and firmware backgrounds alongside cloud and
        application developers — which means we can design the full stack from
        microcontroller firmware to the dashboard your operations team watches
        in real time. We don't hand off at the hardware layer or outsource the
        cloud integration; we own the entire system.
      </p>
      <p>
        The UAE's climate presents specific engineering challenges for IoT
        deployments. Extreme heat, humidity in coastal areas, and the dust
        environment common across industrial and construction sites require
        hardware selection and enclosure design that goes beyond what's adequate
        in more temperate climates. We factor these environmental conditions
        into every deployment recommendation and have direct experience with
        systems operating in UAE industrial and outdoor environments.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond hardware integration, a robust IoT system requires careful
        attention to data architecture — how sensor data is transmitted, stored,
        processed, and presented — as well as security, since connected devices
        are an increasingly common attack surface. We design IoT systems with
        security by default: encrypted device communication, secure OTA update
        mechanisms, device authentication, and anomaly detection for unusual
        behavior patterns.
      </p>

